}
5. Logic for Seek-Bar Synchronization
To avoid high network traffic, use the Reference Point Formula:

Client sends: position: 45000ms, timestamp: 1000500ms.

Server calculates local display: currentDisplayPos = 45000 + (SystemClock.elapsedRealtime() - 1000500).

This ensures the seek bar on the watch moves smoothly without constant updates over the air.

6. Instructions for the AI Assistant (Codex/Cursor)
MediaController Integration: In the Client role, use MediaSessionManager to retrieve the MediaController for the active app.

Callback Management: Ensure callbacks are properly unRegistered when the WebSocket disconnects or the active app changes to prevent memory leaks.

Proxy Session: On the Server side, the MediaSession should have MediaSession.Token linked to the MediaStyle notification.

Error Handling: Handle cases where the Client has multiple media apps open (prioritize the one with PlaybackState.STATE_PLAYING).